// Semantic direction:
// Myhill_Nerode: a language L is regular iff the equivalence x ~_L y (∀z: xz∈L ↔ yz∈L) has
//   finitely many classes — this characterises regular languages and gives the minimal DFA.
// syntaktisk_monoid: the transition monoid of a DFA — the algebraic characterisation of regularity.
// Kleene_algebra: (K, +, ·, *, 0, 1) satisfying 1+aa* = a* and least-fixed-point laws.
// CYK_algoritme: Cocke-Younger-Kasami O(n³) parsing for CFGs in Chomsky normal form.
// Büchi_automat: accepts infinite words if accepting state visited infinitely often — for ω-languages.
// Parity_automat: generalises Büchi/Rabin/Muller — accept if max (or min) infinitely visited colour is even.
// tre_automater: generalise FA to trees — used in XML validation and program analysis.
// vektede_automater: each transition carries a weight from a semiring — subsumes probabilistic FA.
// Angluins_L_stjerne: active learning algorithm that learns a DFA in polynomial time with membership/equivalence queries.
// omega_automater: automata on infinite words — fundamental for reactive program verification.

// Primitive flow:
// minimal_DFA(L) = DFA der tilstander er Myhill-Nerode ekvivalensklasser
// CYK(w, G) = DP-tabell T[i,j,A] = sant iff A ⟹* w[i..j]
// Büchi_aksept(w) = ∃uendelig_løkke: q_f ∈ aksept_tilstander besøkt uendelig

